President Trump has declared a state of emergency in California due to the wildfires that began on December 4, 2017. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts. The assistance provided will help alleviate the hardships faced by the local population and provide necessary emergency measures to save lives and protect property. FEMA is authorized to identify and provide equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be at 75%. Mark Armstrong has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.